The following sections provide a comprehensive overview of the subfolders within the `assets/` directory.

### Subfolders Description

This section provides a quick explanation of each subfolder within the `assets/` folder. Detailed information is provided in their dedicated `.fs-info` files, if available.

#### audio/

The `audio/` subfolder contains audio files such as background music, sound effects, and voiceovers. These files are used to provide auditory feedback and enhance the application's interactivity.

#### icons/

The `icons/` subfolder stores icon files used throughout the application, including social media icons, navigation icons, and other graphical elements.

#### images/

The `images/` subfolder houses image files, including application icons, background images, product images, and placeholders. These resources are used to enhance the application's visual appeal.

#### videos/

The `videos/` subfolder contains video files for tutorials, promotional content, and archived recordings. These files are used to provide visual demonstrations and enrich the user experience.
